      "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion - June 22, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The ElizaOS community discussed several topics on June 22, 2026. A Ruby Trivia initiative was announced and promoted, with trivia challenges shared publicly on social media covering topics such as Marvel Comics and stock market history. Community members engaged with these posts as part of an ongoing engagement effort.",
          "sources": [
            "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241"
          ],
          "images": [],
          "videos": [],
          "posters": [
            "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1782180092605-95l24n.png"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Questions arose regarding the ElizaOS token and foundation. One community member asked whether the foundation planned to add liquidity for trading ElizaOS on the Solana chain. A core developer responded that they do not communicate directly with the foundation, though they confirmed the foundation manages the token. The identity of foundation members was also inquired about but not answered. Separately, a notable on-chain event was flagged by a community member who observed large token movements from a wallet associated with Shaw, which had been dormant for approximately eight months and moved from 1.02 billion tokens to zero. Other members noted the migration occurred around November or December, roughly seven months prior, and acknowledged the legitimacy of the question given the wallet's long period of inactivity.",
          "sources": [
            "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241"
          ],
          "images": [],
          "videos": []
        },
        {
          "text": "A community member asked whether Eliza Cloud or ElizaOS could be expected in 2026. Another member emphasized using the name ElizaOS, describing it as an operating system for AI agents designed to be accessible to everyone. A developer also posted in the community asking if anyone was looking to hire, and another member inquired about the type of development work being sought. A new member introduced themselves as brand new to Eliza and expressed gratitude for being welcomed into the community.",
          "sources": [
            "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241"
          ],
          "images": [],
          "videos": [],
          "posters": [
            "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1782180155830-hquw3r.png"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "In the coders channel, a single greeting was posted by a community member with no further technical discussion recorded for the day.",
